    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel (Live Patch 31 for SLE 12)",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 3.12.61-52_119 fixes several issues.\n\nThe following security issue was fixed:\n\n- CVE-2017-15649: net/packet/af_packet.c in the Linux kernel allowed local users to gain privileges via crafted system calls that trigger mishandling of packet_fanout data structures, because of a race condition (involving fanout_add and packet_do_bind) that leads to a use-after-free, a different vulnerability than CVE-2017-6346 (bsc#1064392)\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
